PN,41809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1782317940
OL,3,CArrest of Donaldson came at the height
OL,4,Cof his political powers
OL,6,FHe refused to back a deal that
OL,7,Fproposed the early release of
OL,8,Fparamilitary prisoners but did not
OL,9,Finclude firm commitments to
OL,10,Fdecommission terrorist weapons.
OL,12,FThe former UDR soldier also had
OL,13,Fconcerns about the establishment of a
OL,14,Fcommission on the future of policing
OL,15,Fand the prospect of the Royal Ulster
OL,16,FConstabulary (RUC) being disbanded.
OL,18,FHis relationship with then UUP leader
OL,19,FDavid Trimble began to crumble from
OL,20,Fthat point on.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/22
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
