OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1782317940
OL,3,CArrest of Donaldson came at the height
OL,4,Cof his political powers
OL,6,FAlthough Donaldson was more
OL,7,Fexperienced and higher profile than Ms
OL,8,FFoster when they joined the ranks of
OL,9,Fthe DUP, she would go on to eclipse
OL,10,Fhim in terms of influence in the two
OL,11,Fdecades that followed.
OL,13,FDonaldson did assume a senior role
OL,14,Fwith the party ` and his thinking
OL,15,Ffactored into many of its key
OL,16,Fstrategic decisions ` but being based
OL,17,Fat Westminster sometimes saw him cast
OL,18,Fas a peripheral figure who was
OL,19,Fdetached from the cut and thrust of
OL,20,Fdevolved politics back at Stormont.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/22
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
