OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1782317940
OL,3,CArrest of Donaldson came at the height
OL,4,Cof his political powers
OL,6,FAs the party chief whip at
OL,7,FWestminster, he was heavily involved
OL,8,Fin negotiations that led to the DUP/
OL,9,FConservative confidence and supply
OL,10,Fagreement and, when it came to
OL,11,Fannouncing the deal, it was him and
OL,12,Fhis Conservative counterpart Gavin
OL,13,FWilliamson who signed on the dotted
OL,14,Fline and shook hands for the cameras
OL,15,Fwhile Ms Foster and Ms May watched on.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G15/22
